## HeroUI Design Guidelines

### Component Usage

**ALWAYS** use HeroUI components instead of plain HTML elements:

```tsx
// ‚úÖ GOOD - Use HeroUI components
import { Card, CardBody } from "@heroui/card";
import { Divider } from "@heroui/divider";
import { Button } from "@heroui/button";
import { Link } from "@heroui/link";

// ‚ùå BAD - Don't use plain HTML
<div className="card">
<hr />
<button>
<a href="...">
```

### Typography System

Use the project's typography primitives defined with `tailwind-variants`:

```tsx
import { title, subtitle } from "@/components/primitives";

// Title variants
<h1 className={title()}>Default title</h1>
<h1 className={title({ size: "lg" })}>Large title</h1>
<h1 className={title({ size: "sm" })}>Small title</h1>
<h1 className={title({ color: "violet" })}>Colored title</h1>

// Subtitle usage
<p className={subtitle()}>Subtitle text</p>
<p className={subtitle({ class: "text-default-600" })}>Custom subtitle</p>
```

### Color Tokens

